tress plausible here). From what I can tell, the market channel was an OOC creation that was meant to further trading and selling of items before the bazaar was implemented and has hung on as kind of a &quot;catch all&quot; channel that is used for /auc, advice, game issues and whatnot. Like I said, I don't mind some IC stuff in the market, but don't bash others for not specifying OOC or putting their text in brackets. If you want to be purely RP and enforce that on others then stay out of the market - it is not RP.<br><br>Also, if you are auctioning WTB for something so high-end that only 2-4 guilds on this server are able to even obtain it (with the exception of SH) you don't need to spam us every 20 secs with a WTB auction. In fact, you would be better served by posting a message in the marketplace here or limiting your messages to once every 10 minutes. I get sick of hearing WTB: Primal Spear or something of that nature every 20 secs and I am loath to use ignore except for real pains-in-the-a$$.<br>Vulrath Vadrigaar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umylodifv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MylodiFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/19/02 8:54:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1420.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Market Channel</span><hr size=1> It should be an unwritten rule that all repeated shouts/auctions/messages should have a time limit of five minutes.  If the market channel were moderated, I'm certain it would be that way.  <p>Mylodi ScarlettFyre, Bard of 41 cycles<br>Proud member of <a href=http://pub38.ezboard.com/bKeepersoftheSilentOath>Keepers of the Silent Oath</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=t