 to an inherently non-RP channel.<br><br>Cross zone shouting in this case means across 2 or more zones. I play a lot in FM and most of the time, I am the only one there. It wouldn't be feasible for me to wander zone-to-zone shouting for help, especially if (if we are still following my example) I am nearly blind because of my graphics problem (this is just an example of an OOC use which is necessary - there are many others).<br><br>I am not saying RP sucks in any way, shape or form. I am and have always advocated a distinction between RP and non-RP. I recognize the value of each, I feel they should be kept seperate and distinct and I feel that there are places and times where each should or shouldn't be used. You can't avoid the facts that market was created to be and still is an OOC arena. I still haven't heard a RP justification for its existence which is necessary if you are going to argue this point. RP should be based on the world of Everquest, and in this world, there is no GOOD way to explain Market, so that by definition negates its validity as an RP arena.<br>I don't want to make RPers unwelcome, but on the other side I don't feel RPers comming into a non-RP forum and flaming people for being OOC is right. That's like joining a running club and announcing at your weekly meeting &quot;Running sucks, I don't do it and neither should you and if you do I will yell at you. We should all rollerblade instead and since *I* am a member of this club, we should do what *I* want because otherwise you are excluding me and making *me* feel uncomfortable.&quot; Yea, but you are still a member of a *running* club.<br><br>You must be able to separate RP from non-RP and accept the use of both. If you get completely immersed in RP you can get in trouble like those people down it the steam tunnels under Princeton or whatever college during the 70's.<br>Vulrath<br><br>Edit: Fixed grammar, added final paragraph <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uth